irly\nnoisy and sparse data, the underlying alignment with shear field is strong\nenough to be visible even when small numbers of galaxies are considered -\nespecially if those galaxies are used as constraints in the reconstruction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Dec 2015 21:00:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Dec 2015 04:07:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-27"}
