r five objects, where\n$\\mathscr{\\dot M}_{f=1}=\\dot M_{\\bullet}/L_{\\rm{Edd}}c^{-2}$ as $f=1$ is\nassumed to estimate $M_{\\rm{RM}}$ used in the Eddington luminosity\n$L_{\\rm{Edd}}$, $\\dot M_{\\bullet}$ is the mass accretion rate, and $c$ is the\nspeed of light. These larger $f$ values will produce higher $M_{\\rm{RM}}$\nvalues and lower Eddington ratios.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Dec 2015 12:46:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Mar 2016 11:42:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 12 Apr 2016 02:40:23 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2016 08:52:15 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2016 08:47:10 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Sun, 2 Oct 2016 07:43:05 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Sun, 20 Nov 2016 10:24:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-06"}
